Windows 11 Emoji Font for Windows 10
Manually install the Windows 11-style flat emoji font on Windows 10.

What This Does
Replaces your Windows 10 Segoe UI Emoji font with the updated flat-style emoji font from Windows 11.

Disclaimer
Always backup your original font before making changes

A system restart may be required

Works on Windows 10 only

Manual Installation Instructions
Step 1: Download the Font
Download the font file from:

https://raw.githubusercontent.com/einzig-diego/Random-Stuff/refs/heads/main/Windows%2011%20Emojis/seguiemj.ttf

Save it somewhere easy to find (like your Downloads folder or Desktop).

Step 2: Backup Your Original Font
Open File Explorer and navigate to:

C:\Windows\Fonts

Find any files named:

seguiemj.ttf (or similar emoji-related .ttf files)

Copy these files to a backup folder (e.g., C:\EmojiFontBackup or your Desktop)

Step 3: Install the New Font
Method A: Drag and Drop (Easiest)

Open C:\Windows\Fonts in File Explorer

Drag the downloaded seguiemj.ttf file into the Fonts folder

Windows will automatically install it (may ask for administrator permission)

Method B: Right-click Install

Right-click the downloaded seguiemj.ttf file

Select Install

Method C: Copy via Command Prompt (Administrator)

copy "%USERPROFILE%\Downloads\seguiemj.ttf" C:\Windows\Fonts\

Step 4: Verify Installation
Go to C:\Windows\Fonts

Look for "Segoe UI Emoji" in the list

The font should show flat/modern emoji when previewed

Step 5: Restart (Recommended)
Restart your computer to ensure all applications recognize the new font.

How to Restore Original Font
Open C:\Windows\Fonts

Find and delete the new Segoe UI Emoji font

Copy your backed-up original font files back into C:\Windows\Fonts

Restart your computer

Registry Information (Advanced)
If drag-and-drop doesn't work, you can manually register the font:

Press Win + R, type regedit, press Enter

Navigate to:

HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Fonts

Add a new String Value named:

Segoe UI Emoji (TrueType)

Set the value to: seguiemj.ttf

Troubleshooting
Font doesn't appear in applications:

Restart your computer

Clear font cache: Delete everything in C:\Windows\ServiceProfiles\LocalService\AppData\Local\FontCache

Permission denied:

Run File Explorer as Administrator

Right-click → Run as administrator

Font looks corrupted:

Restore your backup font

Redownload the font file (might be corrupted)

Source
Font provided by einzig-diego/Random-Stuff GitHub repository.
